w up in meeting modals, ⌘K quick previews, and record activity timelines.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://attio.com/changelog">https://attio.com/changelog</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:73:"Attio adds associated notes in meetings | Read fresh CRM news on WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:73:"Attio adds associated notes in meetings | Read fresh CRM news on WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:5:"attio";s:4:"href";s:36:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/attio/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:34:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:74:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-adds-associated-notes-in-meetings/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:78:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-adds-associated-notes-in-meetings/#comments";}i:3;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:50;s:5:"title";s:50:"Attio expands Emails to Deals and Custom Objects";s:4:"href";s:78:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-expands-emails-to-deals-and-custom-objects/";s:13:"href-original";s:78:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-expands-emails-to-deals-and-custom-objects/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1768569289;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1768569286;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:569:"<p>Attio rolled out Emails across all record types, including Deals and Custom Objects, extending email tracking beyond standard objects.</p>
<h3>How it works</h3>
<p>Teams can configure multiple email tabs per object to organize messages by use case (e. g., all company email vs. a specific contact thread). Email relevance can be determined via linked company domains and the email addresses of linked people or users. The update is available on mobile as well.</p>
<p>Learn more: <a href="https://attio.com/changelog">https://attio.com/changelog</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:168:"Attio rolled out Emails across all record types, including Deals and Custom Objects, extending email tracking beyond standard objects. | Read fresh CRM news on WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:168:"Attio rolled out Emails across all record types, including Deals and Custom Objects, extending email tracking beyond standard objects. | Read fresh CRM news on WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:5:"attio";s:4:"href";s:36:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/attio/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:34:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:83:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-expands-emails-to-deals-and-custom-objects/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:87:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-expands-emails-to-deals-and-custom-objects/#comments";}i:4;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:10;s:5:"title";s:45:"Attio Adds Meeting Overview to Quick Actions";s:4:"href";s:75:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-crm-meeting-management-in-quick-actions/";s:13:"href-original";s:75:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-crm-meeting-management-in-quick-actions/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1747827899;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1747827768;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:824:"<p><a href="https://www.attio.com/?r=-7hFRgCS6dZ2pDVW/">Attio</a> just made managing meetings simpler with a new update to Quick actions. Now, when you open Quick actions and select “View upcoming meetings,” you’ll see a streamlined view of all your meetings for today and tomorrow — all in one place.</p>
<p>The view includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Meeting times and calendar info</li>
<li>Recording status and controls</li>
<li>Participant lists and attendance tracking</li>
</ul>
<p>You can quickly review your day, confirm who’s joining, and toggle recordings on or off ahead of time — helpful for teams that record selectively for privacy or documentation.</p>
<p>This makes it easier to prepare before calls, avoid missing key recordings, and stay in control without jumping between tools.</p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:166:"Attio adds meeting management to Quick actions. View, prepare, and control recordings for today’s and tomorrow’s meetings — all from one centralized screen.";s:12:"snippet-text";s:166:"Attio adds meeting management to Quick actions. View, prepare, and control recordings for today’s and tomorrow’s meetings — all from one centralized screen.";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:2:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:5:"attio";s:4:"href";s:36:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/attio/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:80:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-crm-meeting-management-in-quick-actions/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:84:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-crm-meeting-management-in-quick-actions/#comments";}i:5;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:4;s:5:"title";s:68:"Attio Rolls Out Desktop Version: Faster CRM Access for Focused Work";s:4:"href";s:47:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-desktop-app/";s:13:"href-original";s:47:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-desktop-app/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1746533960;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1746533706;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1108:"<p>Attio has released a desktop version of their CRM app, giving users a faster and more stable way to work with their sales data outside the browser.</p>
<p>The desktop version is available for both macOS and Windows. It mirrors the full web functionality but brings smoother performance and better multitasking — especially valuable for teams spending hours in CRM each day.</p>
<p>For those who prefer to keep essential tools separate from browser clutter or want to reduce distractions, the native desktop app offers a more focused workflow. Users can switch between pipelines, search contacts, and track conversations without worrying about tab overload or accidental refreshes.</p>
<p>This update fits naturally into Attio’s product direction — keeping things fast, lightweight, and customizable for modern go-to-market teams.</p>
<p>For now, the web and mobile apps remain unchanged. But if you rely on Attio daily, it’s worth trying the desktop experience.</p>
<p>You can download app here: <a href="https://attio.com/download">https://attio.com/download</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:154:"Attio launches a desktop app for Mac, iOS and Androind offering faster CRM access, better multitasking, and a cleaner workspace outside the browser.";s:12:"snippet-text";s:154:"Attio launches a desktop app for Mac, iOS and Androind offering faster CRM access, better multitasking, and a cleaner workspace outside the browser.";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:2:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:5:"attio";s:4:"href";s:36:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/attio/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:52:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-desktop-app/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:56:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/attio-desktop-app/#comments";}}s:11:"pages_ctree";a:5:{s:9:"timeline?";b:1;s:5:"count";i:1;s:4:"this";i:1;s:13:"earlier-title";s:7:"Earlier";s:11:"later-title";s:5:"Later";}}